<h2 id="download-unity-assets">Download Unity Assets</h2>
<p>First get the <a href="https://github.com/OpenMLTD/MLTDTools/" target="_blank">MLTDTools</a>, and run â€œManifestTools.exeâ€.<br />
Then click â€œFileâ€ -&gt; â€œOpenâ€ -&gt; â€œRemoteâ€.</p>

<p><img src="../assets/img/misc/20220421184255.png" width="60%" /></p>

<p>After retrieving the asset list, slide down to assets starting with â€œsong3â€.</p>

<p><img src="../assets/img/misc/20220421185443.png" width="50%" /></p>

<p>Some songs only have one file, such as Fermata in Rapsodia in the image above. (It is weird since the off-vocal version is in the in-game sound player)</p>

<p>Some songs contain more than one files, those are for â€œä¸€éƒ¨æ­Œã„åˆ†ã‘â€. 
Usually there are:</p>
<ul>
  <li>One preview version;</li>
  <li>Different vocal parts;</li>
  <li>One off-vocal version.</li>
</ul>

<p><br />
After right click on assets and add them to the Pending Downloads list, go to the â€œActionâ€ -&gt; â€œDownload Selected Assetsâ€.</p>

<h2 id="unity3d-acb-assets-to-wav">Unity3d ACB Assets to WAV</h2>
<p>To convert acb.unity3d files to acb files, there is an â€œExtractAcb.exeâ€ in the MLTDTools folder.
Just drag acb.unity3d files on it.</p>

<p><br />
After converted those acb.unity3d files to acb files, we need to decrypt them to obtain the WAV files.</p>

<p><a href="https://github.com/Rieksee/acbDecrypter" target="_blank">https://github.com/Rieksee/acbDecrypter</a></p>

<p>Run â€œacbDecrypter.exeâ€ in CMD and follow the instruction, those ACB files will be converted to WAV files.</p>

<p><br />
*Note: The â€œhcaToWav/å¾©å·éµãƒªã‚¹ãƒˆ.txtâ€ file contains a decrypt key for MLTD, and I could confirm that it works in April, 2022.</p>
